== 7...a6 ==

'''7...a6''' kicks White's knight. 

Its available squares are d4 or a3. 

The most common move is [[/8. Na3|'''8. Na3''']]. This places a knight on the rim, but at least it overdefends c4 in case Black hopes to make use of the half-open file and play ...Rc8 one day. 

'''8. Nd4''' reduces White's control of d5, and allows Black to untangle with 8...d5 9. cxd5 exd5 10. exd5 Nxd5 11. Nxc6 bxc6{{Chess/not}} (see diagram). The position is equal but now open, and White is no longer able to keep Black suffocating in their side of the board as they had hoped. 

